&lt;h2&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Behind many of life’s most important transactions — buying a house, applying for a mortgage, getting a small business loan, or refinancing a credit card — is a network of credit relationships. Setpoint is building the critical infrastructure that powers these transactions, helping the world’s leading banks, lenders, and capital providers move with greater speed, trust, and transparency.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re looking for a &lt;strong&gt;Strategic Finance Associate&lt;/strong&gt; to join our Finance team and serve as a true business generalist. This is not a narrow FP&amp;amp;A role — you’ll partner directly with the VP of Finance and play a critical part in driving company-wide initiatives. From shaping financial strategy to supporting day-to-day operations, you’ll be trusted to take on whatever the business needs most at any given moment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a high-impact, highly visible role where no two days look the same. You’ll build financial models, prepare board materials, support cross-functional projects, and step in as a problem-solver for the company’s most pressing priorities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who Will Love This Job&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;A self-starter: &lt;/strong&gt;You thrive with autonomy and enjoy owning complex projects end-to-end.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;A structured thinker: &lt;/strong&gt;You can bring clarity to ambiguous problems and communicate clearly with stakeholders.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;A sharp analyst:&lt;/strong&gt; You love digging into data and building financial models that drive key decisions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;A cross-functional collaborator: &lt;/strong&gt;You enjoy working closely with sales, operations, product, and engineering teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;A builder: &lt;/strong&gt;You&#39;re excited about scaling finance at a fast-growing company.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner cross-functionally with Sales, Operations, Product, and Engineering to ensure alignment between financial goals and day-to-day execution.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive financial visibility by owning reporting, forecasting, KPI setting, and board-ready communications.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead strategic projects that require both financial rigor and operational follow-through — from building models to coordinating implementation across teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Step into critical gaps in company operations: streamline processes, improve internal systems, and ensure execution on key initiatives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Act as a force multiplier for leadership by tackling high-priority projects (strategic finance, operations, or special projects) and ensuring nothing falls through the cracks.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You Should Have&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;4-5 years of relevant work experience with at least 2 years in Investment banking or Management Consulting and ideally, 2 years in a high-growth startup.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong financial modeling skills and Excel proficiency.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent presentation and communication skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to manage multiple priorities and drive projects independently.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience partnering with non-finance teams and explaining financial concepts to cross-functional stakeholders.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
